Tony Okafor, Awka An Igbo group, Ndigbo Patriotic Association, has urged non-indigenes in Ondo state to vote for the incumbent governor, Rotimi Akeredolu in the Saturday poll. The group said the governor deserved a second term putting into consideration his development strides in the state. Speaking with newsmen on Wednesday in Onitsha, President General of the group, Obinna Okeke described Akeredolu as forthright saying the state would be better off if they reelected him Okeke said “The people of the state are privileged to have such a forthright and honest man as governor. “All Ndigbo and other non-indigenes should troop out en masse on Saturday to cast their votes for Akeredolu for continuity and sustainability of his laudable programmes.” Copyright PUNCH.
